From 48bca1264065fb8307ece17fcadeb80121d78895 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Roopni Devanathan <quic_rdevanat@quicinc.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Mar 2025 15:28:13 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK: PROTOCOL: hostapd: Fix memleak issue in radius
 server

For each EAP session, a set of variables are allocated memory. Before
going to the successive session, the previous session's memory must be
deallocated. But, currently, memory allocated for accept_attr is not
deallocated before moving the the next session, resulting in memory leak.

Fix this by freeing the allocated memory before allocating memory for
accept_attr in the next session.

Depends-on: None
Fixes: None

Signed-off-by: Roopni Devanathan <quic_rdevanat@quicinc.com>
---
 src/radius/radius_server.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/radius/radius_server.c b/src/radius/radius_server.c
index 95a1cb9..6d95c13 100644
--- a/src/radius/radius_server.c
+++ b/src/radius/radius_server.c
@@ -2562,6 +2562,7 @@ static int radius_server_get_eap_user(void *ctx, const u8 *identity,
 	ret = data->get_eap_user(data->conf_ctx, identity, identity_len,
 				 phase2, user);
 	if (ret == 0 && user) {
+		os_free(sess->accept_attr);
 		sess->accept_attr = radius_server_copy_attr(user->accept_attr);
 		sess->remediation = user->remediation;
 		sess->macacl = user->macacl;
-- 
